properties.Title: Tropical Cyclone Information Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: For Hurricane Humberto. The next information statement will be issued by 03:00 p.m. ADT. Humberto will affect Bermuda later today and Thursday. It will reach Canadian marine waters Friday, likely affecting the Scotian Slope on Friday, and then parts of the Grand Banks during the weekend. 1. Summary of basic information at 09:00 a.m. ADT. Location: 31.9 North 68.9 West. About 400 kilometres west of Bermuda. Maximum sustained winds: 185 kilometres per hour. Present movement: East-northeast at 26 kilometres per hour. Minimum central pressure: 951 millibars. 2. Public weather impacts and warnings summary. At this time no significant effects are expected over land. a. Wind. No significant wind expected. b. Rainfall. No significant rain expected. c. Surge/Waves. Some swells may affect southern Newfoundland this weekend. 3. Marine weather impacts and warnings summary. Gale to Storm Force winds are likely over parts of the Scotian Slope waters , Laurentian Fan, Banquereau Friday into Saturday, and then parts of the Grand Banks this weekend. Forecaster(s): Couturier. ### Please continue to monitor alerts issued by the Canadian Hurricane Centre and forecasts issued by Environment Canada.
Expires: 2019-09-19T19:03:19-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2019-09-18T13:04:19-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.3754931920.2019
